{"id":13579,"date":"2020-08-20T20:17:22","date_gmt":"2020-08-21T03:17:22","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/?p=13579"},"modified":"2024-01-06T20:30:47","modified_gmt":"2024-01-07T04:30:47","slug":"butter-trails","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/08\/20\/butter-trails\/","title":{"rendered":"BUTTER TRAILS"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>These are two connected mountain bike trails on the side of Nakusp Ridge north of Roseberry. The West Wilson Creek FSR provides access to the Upper Butter trailhead and a connector road connects the Upper and Lower parts. <\/em><\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><em>Both are hand-built single-track flow trails fun for all abilities. Shuttle or bike up the logging road for a 2-3 hour round trip.<\/em> <\/span><br \/>\n<strong><br \/>\nUPPER BUTTER TRAIL<br \/>\n<\/strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The upper half of this trail network is easily accessed by a logging road. It follows the ridge line down giving panoramic views. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Location:<\/strong> Above and east of Roseberry and Slocan Lake. Valhalla Provincial Park is across the lake. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> Easy A1<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation Gain:<\/strong> +67m climb, -372m descent <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Key Elevations:<\/strong> Highest elevation 1,035m<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> 3.7kms<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 1 hour one way<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> June through October <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Access:<\/strong> Mediocre 4WD or AWD high clearance gravel forest service road with steep, loose sections. \u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Map:<\/strong> 82K\/3<\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive:<\/strong> Drive north on Highway 6 from New Denver. Just after crossing the Wilson Creek bridge in Roseberry, turn right on the West Wilson Creek FSR. It follows the south boundary of Roseberry Provincial Park. Take the first acute switchback to the left. From here the road climbs 7.7 km and climbs 851m (-102m) to follow the east side of the ridge high above Roseberry. Park at the first shuttle parking area where the trail and road meet.<br \/>\n<\/span><strong>Route\/Trail:<\/strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"> The upper trail follows the ridge line for 3.7 km to meet the connector road. Turn right onto the road. Follow it for 1.1 km. It climbs 32m and descends 31 m in total. <\/span><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">At the end turn left onto the Lower Butter Trail. \u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<strong><br \/>\nLOWER BUTTER TRAIL<br \/>\n<\/strong><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">The lower half of a mountain bike trail network, Lower Butter can be either an out-and-back hiking trail or done as a continuation of the Upper Butter Trail accessed by logging road. \u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Location:<\/strong> North of Roseberry descending the side of Nakusp Ridge ending in Roseberry Provincial Park. <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Difficulty:<\/strong> Easy A1<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Elevation Gain:<\/strong> +74m, -520 descent 1456\u2019<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Distance:<\/strong> 3.75kms <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Time:<\/strong> 1 hour <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Season:<\/strong> May through October <\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Access:<\/strong> Out and back \u00a0<\/span><br \/>\n<span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\">Map: 82K\/3 <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Drive:<\/strong> From New Denver, drive north on Highway 6. Just after crossing the Wilson Creek Bridge, turn right onto West Wilson Creek FSR. Park at Roseberry Provincial Park and start on the trail. <\/span><\/p>\n<p><span style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;\"><strong>Trail:<\/strong> Ascend steadily on a single-track mountain bike trail through a large treed forest. Some steeper bits and some avoidable stunts. At 3.75 km, meet the connector road coming from the right and Upper Butter Trail. Turn around and return the way you came.<\/span><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>These are two connected mountain bike trails on the side of Nakusp Ridge north of Roseberry. The West Wilson Creek FSR provides access to the Upper Butter trailhead and a connector road connects the Upper and Lower parts. Both are &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/www.ronperrier.net\/2020\/08\/20\/butter-trails\/\">Continue reading <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"jetpack_post_was_ever_published":false,"_jetpack_newsletter_access":"","_jetpack_dont_email_post_to_subs":false,"_jetpack_ne